snippet: With costly travel fees and bureaucratic hurdles finally eliminated, many islanders who have long wished to go overseas flocked to get plane tickets and passports.
abstract: Cubans flock to immigration offices and travel agencies, eager to take advantage of lifting of government travel restrictions.
lead_paragraph: With costly travel fees and bureaucratic hurdles finally eliminated, many islanders who have long wished to go overseas flocked to get plane tickets and passports.

headline.seo: Cubans Take Advantage of Day 1 of New Travel Rules
headline.main: In First Day of New Rules, Cubans Make Travel Plans
